                            <comment id="17750624" author="smiklosovic" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2023 08:12:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;all of these PRs contain same links but there are version specific links&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.11 &lt;a href=&quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/3.11/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/3.11/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
4.0 &lt;a href=&quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/4.0/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/4.0/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
4.1 &lt;a href=&quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/4.1/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/4.1/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is not version-specific link for 3.0 though. I am not completely sure what link we should use but whatever which is not broken is better than broken. I guess going with &quot;latest&quot; is just fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For trunk, when 5.0 is out, there will be &quot;5.0&quot; link. So for the current trunk I would just use &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/5.0/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/5.0/cassandra/cql/cql_singlefile.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;even it does not work for now but it will once 5.0 is out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but as I am thinking more about this, it is of question whether we want to couple CQL with specific Cassandra major / minor. Because one might in theory use CQL of lower version to connect to a cluster of higher version ... It will be something different when you have e.g. cqlsh from pip but cqlsh we ship with Cassandra should have it version-specific I think.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; what is your opinion?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17750676" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2023 10:02:46 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;but as I am thinking more about this, it is of question whether we want to couple CQL with specific Cassandra major / minor.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it would make more sense to tie them to the CQL version, since that will never change, but I guess that would require reorganizing the docs.  As it stands though, despite having major/minor versions in the name, these all appear to be the same file, so there&apos;s currently nothing to gain by linking them to version-specific files.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17750733" author="bschoeni" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2023 12:34:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smiklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smiklosovic&quot;&gt;smiklosovic&lt;/a&gt; good observations, +1 on using latest&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17750906" author="smiklosovic" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2023 23:23:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In that case we are good to merge. I do not think it is meaningful to require CI run here. I will merge tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
